---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const updated = "2026-05-11";
---
<Base title="Privacy — MediaPorter" description="MediaPorter collects no personal data. This page explains what the app does, what it doesn't, and what third parties it talks to.">
  <section class="section">
    <article class="prose">
      <span class="md-tag accent">## privacy</span>
      <h1 style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="md-comment"># Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>MediaPorter does not collect personal data.</strong> No telemetry, no analytics,
        no crash reports, no "anonymous usage statistics," no account, no sign-in.
      </p>

      <h2>What the app talks to</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Your iPhone, iPad, or iPod touch</strong>, over a USB cable or local Wi-Fi link.
          The app uses the same Apple Mobile Device tunnel that iTunes / Finder used. Communication
          is between your Mac and your device only.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The Movie Database (TMDb)</strong>, over HTTPS, to look up titles, posters,
          season/episode information for the media you choose to port. TMDb requests carry the
          query text and nothing that identifies you. We do not send your IP, device ID, or any
          stable identifier alongside these requests.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What stays on your Mac</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Your media library and any files you drop onto MediaPorter.</li>
        <li>Cached posters, probe results, and metadata used to render the app's UI.</li>
        <li>App preferences (window size, last-used settings, recent device).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>None of the above ever leaves your machine.</p>

      <h2>App Store privacy labels</h2>
      <p>
        On the App Store, MediaPorter is registered as <strong>Data Not Collected</strong> across
        every category Apple offers. If that ever changes, this page changes first and a new app
        version follows.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        MediaPorter is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect any data
        from anyone, including children.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We will update this page if the app's behavior ever changes. The "Last updated" date at
        the top of the page reflects the most recent revision.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions: <a href="mailto:hi@porter.md" class="link">hi@porter.md</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Base>
